Science  and Engineering Research Council (SERC) of A*STAR promotes public sector  research and development in the physical sciences and engineering. At SERC,  we:

 Support  world-class research in A*STAR institutes in a wide range of fields including  communications, AI &amp; data science, cybersecurity, modelling and simulations,  materials, chemicals, microelectronics, manufacturing technologies and  metrology;
 Plan  and promote research in strategic areas to create knowledge and intellectual  property that will drive the development of knowledge-intensive  industries;
 Cultivate  and engage an extensive network of industry partners via various funding schemes  and programmes to facilitate a seamless flow of technologies from conception to  commercialisation.

Job  Description

This  role is required to strategise, organise, and drive A*STAR뭩 R&amp;D initiatives  in digital technologies, such as:
 AI  and Data Science
 Communications  and Internet-of-Things
 Digital  trust technologies (including privacy preservation and distributed ledger  technologies)
 Cybersecurity
 Digital  Twinning and Modelling &amp; Simulations
The  officer will be part of a dynamic Infocomm Cluster team which shapes public  sector research and innovation to deliver economic and societal outcomes for  Singapore through:
 Strategic  planning, coordination, and collaborations in digital technology R&amp;D with  Ministries &amp; Public Agencies partners, Research Institutes, Institutes of  Higher Learning, and industry sectors
 Long-term  R&amp;D planning and stakeholder engagements that shape and contribute directly  to the national R&amp;D agenda (eg. RIE 2025)
 Technology  Foresighting and Masterplanning to optimise R&amp;D investment portfolio and  ensure alignment with national priorities
 R&amp;D  programme strategy development and design, which entails convening relevant  public agencies, enterprises, and research entities (within A*STAR and from  Institutes of Higher Learning) into collaboration programmes and securing  necessary management support and resources for programme
 R&amp;D  programme execution and management, including planning for subsequent technology  translation and commercialisation
 Strategic  development and reviews of digital technology capabilities in A*STAR Research  Institutes
 Research  proposals evaluation, project reviews and grant management
Job  Requirements
 Background  in Engineering, IT or Computer Science with at least 4 to 8 years of working  experience
 Ability  to think strategically, analyse issues from different angles and devise  comprehensive solutions
 Knowledge  in a broad range of digital technologies, the digital industry, their trends,  challenges, and potentials
 Leadership  qualities and ability to mentor junior officers
 Passion  in shaping research and innovation in digital technologies to bring about  economic and societal outcomes for Singapore
 Proactive  learning attitude, attention to details and results-oriented
 Comfortable  with delivering outcomes in complex environment within challenging  timelines